How to use your blending sponge 

* Always apply moisturiser and primer first to your face. This can help prevent soaking in too much makeup.

* Use it wet. Run it under water for a few seconds and rinse it out by squeezing it a few times.

* Put a pea size amount of your foundation, concealer, etc. on the back of your hand and dip your sponge, then use a “bouncing” motion to apply your favorite creams or powders.

* Use a micro mini sponge for area like around your nose, inner eyes, and for precision highlighting and contouring.

* Don’t forget to wash it after every use and let it air dry.
